<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><map version="1.0.1"><node TEXT="Q-Chain"><node TEXT="analytics"><node TEXT="ID:Q-008 | T:What ETL strategies and integration approaches are outlined in the ETL and strategy documents? | C:None | S:asked | D:low | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Review ETL_Audit_Columns_Strategy_v2.1.md and Integration_Design_v1.0.md"/><node TEXT="- Review SCD_Strategy_v2.1.md and Snapshot_Strategy_2.1.md"/><node TEXT="- Review schema_lint.py for validation logic"/></node></node><node TEXT="documentation"><node TEXT="ID:Q-011 | T:What data storage infrastructure is available (SQL Express or Fabric) and how should we provision it for the warehouse? | C:None | S:asked | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Confirm whether SQL Express is installed on the VM or accessible elsewhere"/><node TEXT="- Assess if Microsoft Fabric’s free warehouse tier can serve as the target database"/><node TEXT="- Identify storage limits, connectivity requirements and any setup steps needed"/></node><node TEXT="ID:Q-012 | T:How will we compile and deliver the final YAML summaries for all 19 project documents? | C:None | S:asked | D:high | Depends:Q-006,Q-007,Q-008,Q-009,Q-010"><node TEXT="- Define the YAML schema for each document summary, ensuring consistency with existing plan_zero and project_charter formats"/><node TEXT="- Review and extract key information from each of the 19 documents, noting definitions, requirements, assumptions and tasks"/><node TEXT="- Draft and validate YAML files, incorporating feedback and iterating as needed"/><node TEXT="- Document any gaps or uncertainties for follow‑up"/></node></node><node TEXT="environment"><node TEXT="ID:Q-010 | T:What operational setup and lessons are captured in the landing and storyboard documents? | C:None | S:asked | D:low | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Review README_landing.md and Storyboard.md"/><node TEXT="- Review Plan zero.md and any related README files"/><node TEXT="- Summarise landing zone setup, retention policies, conventions and lessons learned"/></node></node><node TEXT="etl"><node TEXT="ID:Q-007 | T:What data model structures and specifications are defined in the data‑model and spec documents? | C:None | S:asked | D:low | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Review Retail_Data_Model_v2.1.md and Retail_Data_Model_v2.1.dbml.txt"/><node TEXT="- Review Data-Spec_Sheet_v3.3.1.md and Data_Design_v1.0.md"/><node TEXT="- Summarise entities, attributes, relationships and constraints"/></node></node><node TEXT="misc"><node TEXT="ID:T-011-01 | T:T-011-01 | C: | S:pending | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:T-011-02 | T:T-011-02 | C: | S:pending | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:T-011-03 | T:T-011-03 | C: | S:pending | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:T-013-01 | T:T-013-01 | C: | S:pending | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:T-013-02 | T:T-013-02 | C: | S:pending | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:T-013-03 | T:T-013-03 | C: | S:pending | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:T-013-04 | T:T-013-04 | C: | S:pending | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:T-013-05 | T:T-013-05 | C: | S:pending | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-ROOT-01 | T:Ambiguous scope could lead to missing tasks or misaligned priorities. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-001-01 | T:Some files may be missing or contain outdated information. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-001-02 | T:Scope creep if tasks are not clearly bounded. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-002-01 | T:Misinterpreting technical details or missing critical information. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-002-02 | T:Information overload leading to incomplete summaries. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-003-01 | T:Overlooking tasks hidden in technical notes or appendices. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-003-02 | T:Duplicating tasks or mixing deliverables with objectives. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-004-01 | T:Misordered tasks leading to blockers or rework. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-004-02 | T:Missing a critical dependency or decision impacting later phases. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-005-01 | T:Overlooking rework needs, leading to stale or inaccurate project plans. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-005-02 | T:Performing unnecessary revisions that slow progress. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-006-01 | T:Misalignment between vision and scope in different documents. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-006-02 | T:Missing a critical objective or assumption. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-007-01 | T:Misinterpreting entity relationships or missing key fields. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-007-02 | T:Spec mismatches between versions. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-008-01 | T:Overlooking crucial ETL rules or audit requirements. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-008-02 | T:Confusion between different strategy versions. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-009-01 | T:Misinterpreting KPI formulas or omitting required dimensions. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-009-02 | T:Inconsistent KPI naming or definitions across documents. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-010-01 | T:Missing important operational nuance or configuration detail. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-010-02 | T:Not incorporating lessons learned into future tasks. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-011-01 | T:No SQL engine available, causing blockers for ETL development. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-011-02 | T:Underestimating resource limits of the chosen engine. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-012-01 | T:Inconsistent or incomplete summaries leading to confusion. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-012-02 | T:Overlooking critical details from a document. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-013-01 | T:Misplaced files cause 'not found' errors. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-013-02 | T:Non-ASCII filenames break shell/CI quoting. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:E-013-03 | T:Insufficient Drive permissions block imports. | C: | S:noted | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-012-01 | T:All project documents are accessible and can be processed to create summary YAMLs. | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-007-01 | T:The data model and DBML documents correspond to the same version and reflect the current schema (v2.1). | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-007-02 | T:The data specification sheet and data design documents are consistent with the data model and contain no missing columns or mismatches. | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-010-01 | T:The README_landing and Storyboard documents capture all environment setup details, naming conventions, retention policies and lessons learned. | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-001 | T:All uploaded project files are accessible and accurate. | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-008-01 | T:The ETL Audit Columns Strategy v2.1 document represents the final rules for audit columns and meta-table design. | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-008-02 | T:The Integration Design v1.0 document encompasses all source systems and their extraction methods. | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-008-03 | T:The SCD Strategy and Snapshot Strategy documents (v2.1) align with project requirements and cover all dimension and fact loading scenarios. | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-011-01 | T:SQL Express is installed on the VM or accessible through remote connection. | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-011-02 | T:Microsoft Fabric’s free warehouse tier is accessible and can be used as the data warehouse target. | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-011-03 | T:Sample data volumes and resource utilisation fit within the limits of the chosen SQL engine (SQL Express or Fabric free tier). | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-013-01 | T:All project I/O will use /mnt/data as the canonical workspace. | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/><node TEXT="ID:A-013-02 | T:Google Drive connector has read access to the provided folder ID. | C: | S:planned | D:medium | Depends:—"/></node><node TEXT="model"><node TEXT="ID:Q-006 | T:What are the key points and objectives described in the vision and charter documents? | C:None | S:answered | D:low | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Read Vision.md, Project Charter.txt, plan_zero.yaml and project_charter.yaml"/><node TEXT="- Summarise the vision, objectives, scope and timeline"/><node TEXT="- Capture any strategic assumptions or constraints"/></node></node><node TEXT="operations"><node TEXT="ID:Q-009 | T:What KPIs, metrics and definitions are provided in the KPI and trace documents? | C:None | S:asked | D:low | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Review KPI List v3.0.md and KPI_Cards v3.0.md"/><node TEXT="- Review KPI_Trace_Matrix_v3.0.md and Data_KPI_Trace_Matrix_v3.0.md"/><node TEXT="- Summarise definitions, calculations, dimensions and fact mappings"/></node></node><node TEXT="planning"><node TEXT="ID:Q-ROOT | T:Set up the retail analytics project Q‑Chain | C:None | S:asked | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Define the project’s objective and initialise the Q‑Chain"/><node TEXT="- Spawn child questions covering document analysis, task identification and dependency mapping"/></node><node TEXT="ID:Q-001 | T:How should we structure the Q‑Chain to manage the retail data warehouse and analytics project based on the uploaded documents? | C:None | S:asked | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Review all 19 uploaded project files (vision, design docs, KPI lists, audit strategy, etc.)"/><node TEXT="- Identify major questions, tasks and deliverables needed to build the retail data warehouse and KPI dashboards"/><node TEXT="- Define dependencies and decision points across phases (ETL, modelling, dashboarding, governance)"/></node><node TEXT="ID:Q-002 | T:How should we systematically review and summarise the content of all uploaded project files? | C:None | S:asked | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Classify files by type (vision/charter, data models/specs, ETL strategies, KPI definitions, operational docs)"/><node TEXT="- Read each category and summarise the main points, requirements and decisions"/><node TEXT="- Capture any ambiguous or missing information as follow‑up questions or assumptions"/></node><node TEXT="ID:Q-003 | T:What major tasks, deliverables and questions emerge from the project documents for building the retail data warehouse and analytics solution? | C:None | S:answered | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Compile tasks related to ETL meta tables, dimension seeding, merge procedures and staging loaders"/><node TEXT="- Identify higher‑level tasks like snapshot fact loading, SCD automation, performance benchmarking and dashboards"/><node TEXT="- List governance and operational deliverables such as CI/CD, documentation, KPI trace checks and runbook"/></node><node TEXT="ID:Q-004 | T:How should we map dependencies and decision points across the identified tasks and phases? | C:None | S:answered | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Determine prerequisite relationships between tasks (e.g., dimensions before facts, ETL before dashboards)"/><node TEXT="- Identify decision points that influence downstream work (e.g., audit column design, spec choices)"/><node TEXT="- Choose a method to represent and track dependencies (e.g., YAML depends field, Gantt view)"/></node><node TEXT="ID:Q-005 | T:What roadmap should we follow to revisit and refine the Q‑Chain after the initial YAML compilation? | C:None | S:asked | D:low | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Schedule a post‑review cycle to cross‑check the YAML graph against the finalised documents"/><node TEXT="- Identify triggers for rework, such as new files, updated requirements or errors discovered during implementation"/><node TEXT="- Define the update mechanism and version control strategy for refining the YAML graph"/></node></node><node TEXT="tooling"><node TEXT="ID:Q-013 | T:How do we access and standardise project files across tools to avoid sandbox mismatches? | C:connectors | S:answered | D:medium | Depends:—"><node TEXT="- Select a canonical workspace for all I/O"/><node TEXT="- Add a session startup probe to verify mounts and filenames"/><node TEXT="- Define Drive→workspace import flow by folder ID"/><node TEXT="- Enforce ASCII‑hyphen naming and no spaces"/></node></node></node></map>